Since the os.Args in Golang is zero based, os.Args[1] effectively relies on having at least 2 elements in the array. 

{quote}
func main() {
	endpoint := "tcp://localhost:40000"
	if len(os.Args) > 0 {
		endpoint = os.Args[1]
	}

	prefix := intkey.Hexdigest("intkey")[:6]
	handler := intkey.NewIntkeyHandler(prefix)
	processor := processor.NewTransactionProcessor(endpoint)
	processor.AddHandler(handler)
	processor.Start()
}
{quote}

In particular, it panics when "main" is called without the endpoint argument/parameter, this block

https://github.com/hyperledger/sawtooth-core/blob/d40720ec3659c431df6cd5a132c801ada3ceb4aa/sdk/examples/intkey_go/src/sawtooth_intkey/main.go#L11

