Currently, if a transaction fails, the REST API reports that the transaction is PENDING.  This is misleading to the end-user.  

This should return a response with more information:
{code}
{
  "data": {
    "<batch_id>": {
      "status": "PENDING|COMMITED|REJECTED",
      "detail": "<Error message from TP>" | null
    }
  }
}
{code}

The detail is on optional value which, for REJECTED would contain the failure messages returned by the transaction processor.

